Note: Comprehensive Runa Language Specification Compliance Test
Note: This file tests ALL features from the formal grammar specification

Note: ========== BASIC VARIABLE DECLARATIONS ==========
Let user name be "Alice"
Let age be 25
Let balance be 1000.50
Let is active be true
Let null value be null

Note: ========== TYPE ANNOTATIONS ==========
Let integer (Integer) be 42
Let string (String) be "hello"
Let float (Float) be 3.14

Note: ========== ARITHMETIC EXPRESSIONS ==========
Let sum be 10 plus 20
Let difference be 50 minus 25
Let product be 6 multiplied by 7
Let quotient be 100 divided by 4
Let remainder be 17 modulo 5

Note: ========== COMPARISON EXPRESSIONS ==========
Let is equal test be age is equal to 25
Let is greater test be balance is greater than 500
Let is less test be age is less than 30
Let is not equal test be user name is not equal to "Bob"
Let is gte test be age is greater than or equal to 25
Let is lte test be age is less than or equal to 30

Note: ========== LOGICAL EXPRESSIONS ==========
Let and test be is active and age is greater than 18
Let or test be balance is greater than 1000 or age is less than 65
Let not test be is not active

Note: ========== COLLECTION LITERALS ==========
Let number list be list containing 1, 2, 3, 4, 5
Let name list be list containing "Alice", "Bob", "Charlie"
Let mixed list be list containing 1, "hello", true, 3.14

Let user dict be dictionary with:
    name as "Alice"
    age as 25
    active as true

Note: ========== FUNCTION DEFINITIONS ==========
Process called "greet user" that takes name as String returns String:
    Let greeting be "Hello, " plus name plus "!"
    Return greeting

Process called "calculate total" that takes price as Float and tax rate as Float returns Float:
    Let tax amount be price multiplied by tax rate
    Let total be price plus tax amount
    Return total

Note: ========== FUNCTION CALLS ==========
Let greeting message be greet user with name as "Bob"
Display greeting message

Let total price be calculate total with price as 100.0 and tax rate as 0.08
Display "Total: " plus total price

Note: ========== CONDITIONAL STATEMENTS ==========
If age is greater than 18:
    Display "Adult user"
Otherwise if age is equal to 18:
    Display "Just became adult"
Otherwise:
    Display "Minor user"

Note: ========== FOR EACH LOOPS ==========
For each item in number list:
    Display "Number: " plus item

For each user in name list:
    Display "User: " plus user

Note: ========== WHILE LOOPS ==========
Let counter be 0
While counter is less than 3:
    Display "Counter: " plus counter
    Set counter to counter plus 1

Note: ========== PATTERN MATCHING ==========
Match age:
    When 18:
        Display "Just turned 18"
    When 25:
        Display "Quarter century"
    When 30:
        Display "Thirty years old"
    Otherwise:
        Display "Other age"

Note: ========== LIST COMPREHENSIONS ==========
Let squares be list containing x multiplied by x for x in number list

Note: ========== ADVANCED TYPES ==========
Type UserRecord is:
    name as String
    age as Integer
    active as Boolean

Type Color is:
    | Red
    | Green
    | Blue
    | Custom with red as Integer and green as Integer and blue as Integer

Note: ========== STRING FORMATTING ==========
Let formatted message be f"User {user name} is {age} years old"
Display formatted message

Note: ========== DICTIONARY ACCESS ==========
Let user age be user dict at key "age"
Display "User age from dict: " plus user age

Note: ========== LIST INDEXING ==========
Let first number be number list[0]
Let second number be number list[1]
Display "First: " plus first number plus ", Second: " plus second number

Note: ========== COMPLEX EXPRESSIONS ==========
Let complex result be (age plus 5) multiplied by 2 minus (balance divided by 100)
Display "Complex result: " plus complex result

Note: ========== NESTED FUNCTION CALLS ==========
Let nested result be calculate total with price as (50 plus 25) and tax rate as 0.1
Display "Nested result: " plus nested result

Note: ========== CHAINED OPERATIONS ==========
Let processed value be age plus 10 multiplied by 2 minus 5
Display "Processed: " plus processed value

Note: ========== BOOLEAN EXPRESSIONS ==========
Let complex boolean be (age is greater than 20) and (balance is greater than 500) or (user name is equal to "Admin")
Display "Complex boolean: " plus complex boolean

Note: ========== FINAL TEST ==========
Display "All syntax tests completed successfully!"
Display "Runa language specification compliance verified!"